<p>The US military said it struck a boat in the eastern Pacific Ocean that it described as involved in narcotics trafficking, killing two people. Several outlets describe the strike as part of a broader US campaign against suspected drug-trafficking vessels at sea, with reported cumulative deaths in the campaign now at least 128.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/YoGiH8n2IYG4K6Q9hkHEf0x9DuVnUvLIQ5fQWzd0HwN-IkHC2QaoClZCRYzVohnVaCjgNEYeCtaZn2kqmbJ0A2cQSyqCSjj7bWUUPwjTu-DamINsCK37_HOe3N1ei1hKTI5AFuOONu4VbSgtF30SRtWqVgK-vFaKQPP_sh_byjguJK_gN2XXpeO0AJDVWEqqTuragJY' alt='An image used in coverage of a US strike on an alleged drug-trafficking vessel in the eastern Pacific.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Video evidence: US Southern Command posted footage that appears to show a small boat speeding across the water before an explosion engulfs it in flames.</li><li>Recent pattern: DW calls this the second similar strike it has reported since the US captured the then-Venezuelan leader Nicolas Maduro.</li><li>Operation name used in coverage: Firstpost says the wider effort is known as “Operation Southern Spear”.</li><li>Legal dispute: Al Jazeera says the campaign has been condemned as illegal, highlighting a sharp dispute over the legal basis for using lethal force at sea.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>US Southern Command: The command said intelligence confirmed the vessel was traveling on known narco-trafficking routes and taking part in narco-trafficking operations. It said no US personnel were injured. (<a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/us-military-says-it-killed-two-people-strike-suspected-drug-vessel-eastern-2026-02-06/'>Reuters</a>)</li><li>Al Jazeera coverage: The outlet describes the strikes as part of a campaign critics have denounced as illegal, raising concerns about sovereignty and the use of force in international waters. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/2/6/us-military-kills-two-people-in-latest-attack-on-vessel-in-the-pacific'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>Firstpost coverage: The outlet says the US has labeled targets “narco-terrorists,” and argues Washington has not provided evidence or identified those killed in the strikes it reports. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/us-attacks-boat-in-eastern-pacific-kills-2-sailors-under-operation-southern-spear-drug-trafficking-narcoterrorists-13976793.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2026/feb/06/two-killed-us-strike-alleged-drug-boat-pacific-trump'>US military says two killed in strike on alleged drug boat in Pacific</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/2/6/us-military-kills-two-people-in-latest-attack-on-vessel-in-the-pacific'>US military kills two people in latest attack on vessel in the Pacific</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/americas/article/3342605/us-destroys-another-alleged-drug-trafficking-boat-pacific-killing-2'>US destroys another alleged drug boat in Pacific, killing 2</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/us-destroys-alleged-drug-boat-in-eastern-pacific/a-75832540'>US destroys alleged drug boat in eastern Pacific</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/us-attacks-boat-in-eastern-pacific-kills-2-sailors-under-operation-southern-spear-drug-trafficking-narcoterrorists-13976793.html'>US attacks boat in Eastern Pacific, kills 2 sailors</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/us-military-says-it-killed-two-people-strike-suspected-drug-vessel-eastern-2026-02-06/'>The United States Navy strikes a boat suspected of transporting illegal narcotics in the Eastern Pacific, killing two people.</a> - reuters.com</li></ul>